<section class="section">
  <h2 class="section-title">Background</h2>
  <div class="about-grid">
    <div class="about-text prose">
      <p>
        I'm a systems-minded engineer pivoting from manufacturing into backend 
        and systems software development. My journey has been unconventional—from 
        12-hour rotating shifts on the factory floor to designing SCADA infrastructure 
        and building media streaming servers in modern C++.
      </p>
      <p>
        I completed my Computer Science degree with distinction (minor in Embedded Systems) 
        at Deakin University while working full-time. This experience taught me discipline, 
        time management, and how to deliver under pressure.
      </p>
      <p>
        My passion lies at the intersection of <strong>systems programming</strong>, 
        <strong>performance optimization</strong>, and <strong>media technology</strong>. 
        I'm fascinated by how bytes flow through systems—whether that's industrial 
        control data or video streams.
      </p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="about-stats">
      <div class="stat">
        <span class="stat-value">~3</span>
        <span class="stat-label">Years Systems Engineering</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat">
        <span class="stat-value">C++20</span>
        <span class="stat-label">Primary Language Focus</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat">
        <span class="stat-value">2025</span>
        <span class="stat-label">CS Degree Completed</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

